====<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Poem Once</span>====

''Oh Seuss where are you? For this wonderous level is quite askew! From ladders that go up and down to nowhere in the air, to stairs that lead everywhere! From the wonderous arches that are spread all across the floor, to the halls of doors, somewhere there will lead to floating chairs or secret stairs! For wonderous marvels await, from the piano of 5000 keys to paths aplenty! Some paths will lead to long halls, some to ever expanding walls!'' 

''But beware, for even the most seasoned wanderer can find themselves falling in the air! For the object they are standing on can be of suspect. Be careful of tiles red, lest you slip and be sent flying ahead! Or watch out for walls that are green, for they hide sticky tricks that are not always seen! Whatever the trick may be, this level will be guaranteed to be full of liminality!''

==<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Description</span>==

Level 765 is a level that has weird structures and elements in it. The level features designs of random things that can lead to other things and others to nowhere. The paths will always be random in where the direction will go. There will be paths that will be impossible to access or climb due to the directions that can go. 

The gravity on this level can change at any time, anywhere. There is no specific location nor specific time that can change the gravity, nor the amount of gravity that will increase nor decrease. The only consistency for gravity changes in this level is that it will be minor most of the time but there is a very rare chance that it can be severe, creating a minor chance that wanderers can be slightly injured. 
{{Blurimage|file=Dr Suess.webp|caption=Photo of Level 765.|align=right}}
The directions and paths in this level can make one's mild confused and can slowly lead to insanity. There are stairs that often times can lead to nowhere or everywhere, ladders that go up and down that seemingly never end, random floating chairs all across the level, doors that just lead to corridors and halls of more doors, this level can easily get one lost if not make them go insane.

There are also elements within this level that can often be fatal. The most common of which are random red tiles that can fling the wanderer miles away, instantly killing them upon impact. There will also often at times be green walls, which are very sticky and if a wanderer touches the wall will be permanently stuck to it. There will be then a three-hour process in which that wanderer will enter the wall, phase through it, and disappear. It is unknown what happens after that point, but it is presumed that they are dead.

===<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">The Piano of 5000 keys</span>===

Within level 765, there is a very rare chance of encountering a piano with approximately 5000 keys. The piano itself will always have random keys out of order, and there are no pedals. Despite that, the piano will always work. Even if one attempts to ruin the piano, it will always repair itself. No entities as well will spawn near it due to the fear of the piano's effects on them. Despite them not appearing near the piano they will still hear any keys being played and will still be effected by any specific beats.
{{Blurimage|file=Piano Keys 5000.webp|caption=The Piano of 5000 keys.|align=right}}
The effects and results of playing the piano and playing certain keys in order are varying. There are thousands of possible effects/results by playing the keys in a certain order. However there are only 27 known effects, most of which are very minor. However there are a few worth mentioning that can affect the wanderer or level in major capacity.

If one plays in a style similar to the first nine seconds of Bach's Fuga in h, the wanderer will be able to find the nearest '''Wibble-Whum Woggler''' and be able to get anything they desire, with an additional fourth free item if the Woggler knows you played the piano with the specific beat.

Similarly, if one plays in a beat to the words "You are you, and that is true." all '''Hugging Harolds''' within the level will stand completely still and will not attack any wanderers for one hour. Despite the non-hostile state however, one will not be able to touch it as one will become stuck to it.

The final one requires two people to preform. One must be playing the piano with precise beats to the words of the children's poem "The Lamplighter". The other must also speak in a normal tone of voice and read aloud the entire poem as well. When preformed exactly right, both wanderers will be invisible for 12 hours. Neither the Wogglers nor Hugging Harolds will be able to sense any presence of them.


====<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Poem Twice</span>====

''Oh Seuss where are thee? For the creatures that reside here are quite the sight to see! One has all the wonders of the trade, and can give wanderers delights of all kinds. But the other always lurks in the shade, and wanderers must keep sharp their minds. The one who trades can give many different items, always in exchange for something they must give him. The other nasty creature waits in the shadows and lurks for when see the wanderer, they will go berserk!''



==<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Entities </span>==

===<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Wibble-Whum Woggler</span>===

The Wibble-Whum Woggler is a friendly and kind entity. Though it is rare to spot him, he will be more than eager to meet wanderers. Upon one's first meeting with him, he will kindly offer five items of his random choosing. These can range from average backrooms items like [[Object 1|Almond Water]] to very random stuff like violins or record players. Either way however after the first five items, he will demand something in exchange for any future trades. He will demand one item for another random item worth less, two items for something worth more, or three items for a specific item. Upon any future interaction with him after one's intitial interaction, he will always provide three free random items.

The Wibble-Whum Woggler has been proven to be a very helpful entity, as if he spots an injured wanderer or someone else tells him of a nearby injured wanderer, he will immediately come to their aid and no matter what condition they are in, wither it's something minor like a bruise or something major like a broken bone, he will always fix it back to it's original state with no cost whatsoever. He will also warn any wanderers of any nearby potential dangers and will always hint at a potential exit nearby if there is one. 

===<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Hugging Harolds</span>===

{{Blurimage|file=Stairs that lead nowhere..png|caption=Stairs where Hugging Harolds will not appear.|align=right}}A hostile entity, Hugging Harolds are very tall and have four extremely long arms. They will attack wanderers on site and try to entrap them by hugging them until they squeeze the wanderer to death. They are very durable and have been proven to be nearly impossible to kill. They are very fast and strong with only one death ever being documented, where a wanderer had to shoot an entire round of assault rifle bullets straight into the heart of a Hugging Harold.

Despite the dangers of Hugging Harolds, they will rarely ever spawn. They will be guaranteed not to spawn anywhere near the piano, exits, and Wibble-Whum Wogglers. Thanks to the architecture in this level, wanderers will be able to escape them with some ease if they are in any tight spaces or ladders. Hugging Harolds are not able to climb nor fit into any tight spaces.

==<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Groups and Orginizations</span>==

Due to the proven unpredictable nature of level 765 and the entities within it's boundaries, it is impossible to set up a permanent base within it. Though there have been recorded instances of temporary bases, none last more than 48 hours.

====<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Poem Thrice</span>====

''Oh Seuss where are thou? For this level has quite many entrance and exit routes! While there may be only two entrance sites, they both involve some sort of hat! One of which requires wearing red and white, and the other requires to find a book with cats! There are indeed exits, but only two. The first must be achieved after talking to the trader. Only then will appear, a door of blue. The second involves a ladder of red and stairs of green, away from the Harolds that are oh so mean!''

==<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Entrances and Exits</span>==

===<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Entrances</span>===

In levels 0-100, if one ever finds a random red and white striped hat, put it on, and think of a cat balancing on a beach ball for 10 seconds, they will be teleported to this level.

In [[Level 353]], if one finds any books with picture of a cat with a hat and read it all the way through, they will be taken here.

===<span style="font-family:'Comic Sans MS'; color:#FFFFFF; text-shadow: 1px 1px 0 #000000, 2px 2px 1px #000000;">Exits</span>===

If one finds a red ladder leading to green stairs and takes those green stairs, they will be taken to [[Level 180]].

If one asks the Wibble-Whum Woggler where the exit is, he will speak of a blue door not too far. He will not speak where it is, but it will spawn within one mile of talking with him. Enter this door, and one will end up in [[Level 365]].

